data.title: Conduent adds Michael J. Fucci to Board of Directors, effective October 27. Fucci, ex-Deloitte US Chair, has 40+ years of experience in leadership.
data.description: Conduent Incorporated, a leading tech-focused business solutions company (Nasdaq: CNDT), has appointed Michael J. Fucci to its Board of Directors, starting October 27. Fucci, with over 40 years of leadership background, previously held the position of Deloitte US Chair from 2015 to 2019. In this capacity, he was responsible for crucial tasks such as setting enterprise strategy and ensuring leadership success.

data.title: US stock futures rose after a decline on Thursday, with Amazon leading gains. Nasdaq Futures surged 1.21%. Amazon reported net sales of $180.2B, up 13% YoY, and projects $206-213B for Q4, driving its stock up 12.21%.
data.description: U.S. stock futures rose following a previous decline, with major benchmark indices showing gains. Amazon.com Inc. (NASDAQ: AMZN) and Apple Inc. (NASDAQ: AAPL) drove the increase after strong quarterly results. Nasdaq Composite index fell over 350 points due to mixed earnings from Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: META) and Microsoft Corp. (NASDAQ: MSFT). 10-year Treasury bond yielded 4.11% while two-year bond was at 3.61%. CME Group's FedWatch tool showed a 66.8% chance of interest rate cut in December. Futures changes were: Dow Jones 0.11%, S&P 500 0.69%, Nasdaq 100 1.21%, and Russell 2000 -0.03%. SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (NYSE: SPY) and Invesco QQQ Trust ETF (NASDAQ: QQQ) tracking S&P 500 and Nasdaq 100 rose in premarket, with SPY at $685.54 (up 0.84%) and QQQ at $634.65 (up 1.37%). Amazon.com surged 12.21% in premarket after third-quarter net sales of $180.2 billion, predicting fourth-quarter sales between $206.0 billion to $213.0 billion. AMZN maintained a strong price trend in short, medium, and long terms.

data.title: Yonsei University study shows PM2.5 doubles accident risk with 2.6-fold increase and billions in losses.
data.description: Research conducted by scientists from Yonsei University in Seoul, South Korea has revealed a concerning correlation between increased levels of PM2.5 and workplace accidents. The study found that doubling the concentration of PM2.5 in the air is associated with a 2.6-fold higher risk of accidents occurring. This not only poses a threat to the health and safety of workers but also results in significant economic losses. The findings underscore the urgent need for measures to address air pollution and its impact on occupational safety.

data.description: On October 31, 2025, it was reported that the North Pacific Surgical Association revealed Dr. Martin Schreiber as the speaker for the keynote address during the association's yearly conference in Banff, Canada. data.title: Mob Entertainment and TheoryVerse partner to launch "Poppy Playtime X TheoryVerse" apparel collection for gamers. Los Angeles, Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: A collaboration between popular gaming personalities has resulted in the launch of a unique fashion collection designed by and for gamers. data.title: Kids eat free at Dickey's Barbecue Pit this Halloween with an adult meal purchase on October 31, 2025. CEO Laura Rea Dickey shares the Halloween spirit.
data.description: Dickey's Barbecue Pit is offering a special Halloween promotion on Friday, October 31, 2025, where kids eat for free in-store all day with the purchase of an adult meal. The CEO of Dickey’s Barbecue Restaurants, Inc., Laura Rea Dickey, expressed excitement about providing families with a festive and delicious dining experience on this spooky occasion. This promotion is a great way for families to enjoy Texas-style barbecue without any hidden costs, exemplifying the brand's commitment to creating memorable moments for its customers.

data.title: Calix beats Q3 expectations with 44 cents EPS and $265.437 million sales, raises Q4 guidance to $0.35-$0.41 EPS and $267-$273 million sales.
data.description: Calix, Inc. (traded as CALX on NYSE) outperformed expectations with its third-quarter financial results, announced after markets closed on Wednesday. The company reported adjusted earnings of 44 cents per share, surpassing the projected 24 cents per share. Quarterly sales stood at $265.437 million, higher than the anticipated $246.100 million. For the upcoming fourth quarter, Calix foresees adjusted earnings per share in the range of $0.35 to $0.41, exceeding estimates of $0.20. Sales for Q4 are projected to be between $267.000 million and $273.000 million, surpassing expectations of $250.980 million. More details are provided on Benzinga.com.

data.title: TerraMaster to release TOS 7 NAS operating system after 2 years of development, with chance to win new USB4 NVMe SSD drive enclosure D1 SSD Plus.

data.title: AAPL releases new book, Core Versus Chore, to tackle healthcare burnout, inefficiency using human-centered design.
data.description: Today, in Washington on October 31, 2025, the American Association for Physician Leadership (AAPL) revealed the launch of their latest publication, titled Core Versus Chore: Using Human-Centered Design to Address Burnout and Inefficiencies in Healthcare. The book is authored by a distinguished physician leader within the healthcare industry and aims to provide insights on tackling burnout and inefficiencies.

data.title: Palantir co-founder warns that AI giants need more funding every 3-6 months but are afraid to scare investors. Investment underestimation in the AI space.
data.description: Joe Lonsdale, co-founder of Palantir Technologies Inc. (NASDAQ: PLTR), recently expressed concerns that industry leaders in artificial intelligence (AI) are underestimating the resources needed to meet their ambitious goals. Lonsdale, who is also the founder of venture firm 8VC, warned of a continuous cycle every 3-6 months where executives are constantly seeking more capital and energy to drive their initiatives forward. Speaking on CNBC's "Squawk Box," he highlighted that AI companies may be downplaying their true needs out of fear of alarming investors. Lonsdale emphasized the importance of acknowledging the significant investment required in the AI space, indicating that current estimations may fall short of the actual amount needed. This insight reflects a potentially greater demand for resources in the AI industry than previously anticipated.
